📚 MATH ENGINE – QUICK GUIDE 🚀

✨ 1) MAIN EXPRESSION
Type your main formula first – the engine will crunch it!
Example:
   trunc(digits, (426880 * sqrt(10005)) / sum(k, 0, (digits / 14), 1, part1))

🧮 2) VARIABLES
Define values to make formulas cleaner & smarter.
Example:
   digits = 1000
   precision = digits + pct(30, digits)
   part1 = (-1)^k * (6*k)! * (545140134*k + 13591409) / part2
   part2 = (3*k)! * (k!)^3 * 640320^(3*k)

Rules:
   📌 Built-in: `pi` (precision follows math context)
   🆕 User-defined: Must match `[a-zA-Z]([0-9])*`

💻 3) JAVA FUNCTIONS
Write your own logic in Java!
Example:
   public int myfunction(int i) {
       logger.log("something to log");
       return i * 10;
   }

⚙️ 4) SUPPORTED OPERATIONS

➕ Operators:
   ➕ Add            →  2 + 3
   ➖ Subtract       →  5 - 2
   ✖️ Multiply       →  4 * 7
   ➗ Divide         →  10 / 2
   🔼 Power         →  2 ^ 8
   🎯 Factorial     →  5!
   📏 abs(x)        →  abs(-7)
   📐 sqrt(x)       →  sqrt(16)
   📦 cubrt(x)      →  cubrt(27)
   🪜 nthroot(n,x)  →  nthroot(4, 81)
   🎯 pct(n,x)      →  pct(30, 200)
   🔄 recip(x)      →  recip(4)
   📊 logn(n,x)     →  logn(2, 8)
   🚀 exp(x)        →  exp(2)

🛠 Built-in Functions:
   ✂ trunc(n,x)       →  trunc(5, pi)
   Σ  sum(k,start,end,step,expr) → sum(k, 0, 9, 1, k^2)
   🌀 fib(x)         →  fib(5)

📝 5) EXAMPLE WORKFLOW
   1️⃣ Write main expression:
       trunc(digits, (426880 * sqrt(10005)) / sum(k, 0, (digits / 14), 1, part1)) + myfunction(10)
   2️⃣ Define variables(optional):
       digits = 10000
       precision = digits + pct(30, digits)
       part1 = (-1)^k * (6*k)! * (545140134*k + 13591409) / part2
       part2 = (3*k)! * (k!)^3 * 640320^(3*k)
   3️⃣ Define variables(optional):
       public int myfunction(int i) {
           logger.log("something to log");
           return i * 10;
       }
   3️⃣ Hit RUN ✅ and see the magic! ✨

💡 TIP:
Mix variables, constants & functions to create 
anything from quick math to series calculations!
